## 4. Rollback plan

### 4.1 Code rollback (if a solver/backend regression is discovered)

```bash
# Re-pin previous image SHA and recreate
docker compose -f docker-compose.qa.yml up -d --force-recreate
```

### 4.2 Schema rollback (only if the new columns cause unexpected downstream trouble)

Schema rollback is **optional** — the ADD COLUMN changes are additive and
backward-compatible. Old code that doesn't SELECT these columns continues
to work unchanged. But if you specifically want to drop them:

```sql
-- Drop Fix #16 columns (additive — safe to keep; drop only if conflicting)
ALTER TABLE solver_jobs DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS fetch_rt;
ALTER TABLE solver_jobs DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS fetch_ct;
ALTER TABLE planner_assignments DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS category_priority;
-- Index is auto-dropped with the column.
```

Fix #7 schema additions (RT/CT catalog rows) can stay in any case — they
only make the FE's catalog complete; no downside to keeping them.

