## 7. Known non-blockers (document but don't fix)

- Existing `solver_jobs` rows (jobs completed before Fix #16) have
  `fetch_rt=TRUE, fetch_ct=TRUE` (the DEFAULT). This is the "safe" value
  meaning "FE fetches from external DB". New jobs set the correct value
  at trigger time.
- Existing `planner_assignments` rows have `category_priority=NULL`. Only
  rows inserted after Fix #16 populated this column. No backfill needed
  for historical rows — they pre-date the feature.
- 53% coverage in QA scope is a data-quality observation (REN=48 demand,
  0 local supply). Not a solver defect.

